document_title: Voice disorders: Causes, signs and treatments
subsection_content:
Symptoms of voice disorders are quite clear, you can immediately recognize unusual changes in the voice such as:
Voice is shaky, intermittent, less stable; Weak, whispering voice; Voice sounds reluctant, tense or shrill; Voice is too high, too low or changes voice depending on time of day; Hoarseness; Lost voice.
